```
This code declares an integer variable x and initializes it to 10. We then declare a pointer p and assign it the memory address of x using the & operator.

We can also use pointers to dynamically allocate memory on the heap. For example:
```c++
int* p = new int;
*p = 10;
```
This code allocates memory on the heap for an integer and assigns the value 10 to it. We can then access this memory location using the pointer p.

Pointers can also be used to create arrays dynamically on the heap. For example:
```c++
